# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully implemented Vercel Speed Insights for the React + Vite application.

## Changes Made

### 1. Added Dependencies
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package (version 1.1.0)
- Updated `package.json` and `package-lock.json`

### 2. Modified Files
- **src/App.tsx**: 
  - Added `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react';` at the top
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the main App component, nested within the `TooltipProvider` and after the `BrowserRouter`

## Implementation Details

The SpeedInsights component was added following the official Vercel documentation for React applications (create-react-app style). The component is placed at the root level of the application to ensure it tracks all routes and pages.

**Location in component tree:**
```
<ErrorBoundary>
  <QueryClientProvider>
    <TooltipProvider>
      <Toaster />
      <Sonner />
      <BrowserRouter>
        <Routes>...</Routes>
      </BrowserRouter>
      <SpeedInsights /> ← Added here
    </TooltipProvider>
  </QueryClientProvider>
</ErrorBoundary>
```

